review_blob: 16oz Can - Aroma starts out as typical Saison, then surprises you with sweet, cherry notes. Golden color and refreshing taste makes this a great Saison. The plum notes come out on your tongue and are quite nice! I was very please with this brew.
Nice funky sour, very pucker worthy, can taste the oak. Even after a year pours beautiful dark amber.
Very clean visually, but lacks head. Has piney, fruity flavors... aftertaste leaves pine, with some sweet after tones. Nice summer IPA.
